<subSubSection id="C31E656BFFF2FF82B7BD09FEFB4D33D9" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" type="key">
<key id="FF9561D1FFF2FF82B7BD09FEFB4D33D9" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<keyStep id="30F02E45FFF2FF82B7BD09FEFB4D3001" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<paragraph id="8BBB36E0FFF2FF82B7BD09FEFB4D3069" blockId="2.[166,1225,220,702]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<keyLead id="30F595D5FFF2FF82B7BD09FEFB4D3069" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
1. Female fore tarsal claws without basal lobes. Mesosoma partly red. Male hind coxa red and all trochanters yellow (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B67109DAFE37306A" box="[362,435,248,270]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
fig. 3, 
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B6BC09DBFE37306A" box="[423,435,249,270]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). ........................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D63FFF2FF82B34209DBFB4D3069" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[1113,1225,248,270]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Exeristes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficollis">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B34209DBFB4D3069" box="[1113,1225,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">E. ruficollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB36E0FFF2FF82B7BD0837FB4D3001" blockId="2.[166,1225,220,702]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<keyLead id="30F595D5FFF2FF82B7BD0837FB4D3001" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
– Female fore tarsal claws with basal lobes. Mesosoma usually black, if sometimes partly or entirely red, then the ovipositor tip with a subapical tubercle (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B5D90810FD77302C" box="[706,755,306,328]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetId="figure-355@2.[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Exeristes spp., female. 1 — E. roborator, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 3 — E. arundinis, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 4 — E. denticulator, holotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 5 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 6 — E. arundinis, fore tarsal claw (lateral view); 7 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, hind femur and tibia (lateral view); 8 — E. denticulator, holotype, hind tibia and tarsus (lateral view); 9 — E. denticulator, holotype, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view); 10 — E. roborator, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404124/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B5E70810FC833023" box="[764,775,306,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[170,203,1808,1830]" captionTargetBox="[257,1165,1011,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-418@1.[257,1165,1011,1773]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. The Carpathian Exeristes spp. distribution map. Yellow circle — E. roborator; red circle — E. longiseta; green circle — E. arundinis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404122" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404122/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B5E70810FC833023" box="[764,775,306,327]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B4090810FC993023" box="[786,797,306,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B4090810FC993023" box="[786,797,306,327]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Male hind coxa and trochanters variable. If all male trochanters yellow, then hind coxa black. ......................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F02E45FFF2FF82B7BD084EFB4D3376" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<paragraph id="8BBB36E0FFF2FF82B7BD084EFB4C30DE" blockId="2.[166,1225,220,702]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<keyLead id="30F595D5FFF2FF82B7BD084EFB4C30DE" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
2. Female metasomal tergites strongly transverse (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B5A1084EFD6930E6" box="[698,749,364,386]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetId="figure-355@2.[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Exeristes spp., female. 1 — E. roborator, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 3 — E. arundinis, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 4 — E. denticulator, holotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 5 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 6 — E. arundinis, fore tarsal claw (lateral view); 7 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, hind femur and tibia (lateral view); 8 — E. denticulator, holotype, hind tibia and tarsus (lateral view); 9 — E. denticulator, holotype, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view); 10 — E. roborator, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404124/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B5EC084EFC8A30E5" box="[759,782,364,385]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">10</emphasis>
). Ovipositor tip with a subapical tubercle and female fore tarsal claws simple (not emarginated apically). Male clypeus with an apical tubercle (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B38908AAFB4130FA" box="[1170,1221,392,414]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B7E90887FF7930DE" box="[242,253,421,442]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">4</emphasis>
). All male coxae usually black, trochanters red. ....................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D63FFF2FF82B3430884FB4C30DE" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[1112,1224,421,443]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Exeristes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roborator">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B3430884FB4C30DE" box="[1112,1224,421,443]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">E. roborator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB36E0FFF2FF82B7BD08E0FB4D3376" blockId="2.[166,1225,220,702]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<keyLead id="30F595D5FFF2FF82B7BD08E0FB4D3376" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">– Female metasomal tergites subquadrate or elongated. Ovipositor tip without a subapical tubercle or female fore tarsal claws emarginated apically. Male clypeus without an apical tubercle. Male coxae and trochanters variable. ........................................................................................................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F02E45FFF2FF82B7BD0B3AFB4D33D9" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<paragraph id="8BBB36E0FFF2FF82B7BD0B3AFB4D3303" blockId="2.[166,1225,220,702]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<keyLead id="30F595D5FFF2FF82B7BD0B3AFB4D3303" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
3. Tarsomere 5 of hind tarsus about 1.2 times longer than tarsomere 2 (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B4810B3AFC4A334A" box="[922,974,536,558]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B4C20B3BFC60334A" box="[985,996,537,558]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">5</emphasis>
). Ovipositor tip with a subapical tubercle (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B6B20B17FE5E332F" box="[425,474,565,587]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetId="figure-355@2.[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Exeristes spp., female. 1 — E. roborator, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 3 — E. arundinis, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 4 — E. denticulator, holotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 5 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 6 — E. arundinis, fore tarsal claw (lateral view); 7 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, hind femur and tibia (lateral view); 8 — E. denticulator, holotype, hind tibia and tarsus (lateral view); 9 — E. denticulator, holotype, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view); 10 — E. roborator, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404124/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B6F80B17FE6A332E" box="[483,494,565,586]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B6F80B17FE6A332E" box="[483,494,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Female fore tarsal claws emarginated apically (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B4A30B17FC6C332F" box="[952,1000,565,587]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[170,203,1808,1830]" captionTargetBox="[257,1165,1011,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-418@1.[257,1165,1011,1773]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. The Carpathian Exeristes spp. distribution map. Yellow circle — E. roborator; red circle — E. longiseta; green circle — E. arundinis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404122" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404122/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B4E80B17FC7A332E" box="[1011,1022,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">6</emphasis>
). Male scape, pedicel and all coxae black; all trochanters red (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B5700B70FD19330C" box="[619,669,594,616]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B5BC0B70FD363303" box="[679,690,594,615]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[170,203,1808,1830]" captionTargetBox="[257,1165,1011,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-418@1.[257,1165,1011,1773]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. The Carpathian Exeristes spp. distribution map. Yellow circle — E. roborator; red circle — E. longiseta; green circle — E. arundinis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404122" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404122/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B5BC0B70FD363303" box="[679,690,594,615]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). ....................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D63FFF2FF82B34E0B71FB4D3303" baseAuthorityName="Kriechbaumer" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[1109,1225,594,616]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Exeristes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arundinis">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B34E0B71FB4D3303" box="[1109,1225,594,616]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">E. arundinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB36E0FFF2FF82B7BD0B4DFB4D33D9" blockId="2.[166,1225,220,702]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<keyLead id="30F595D5FFF2FF82B7BD0B4DFB4D33D9" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
– Tarsomere 5 of hind tarsus shorter than tarsomere 2 (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B5E70B4DFCAB33E1" box="[764,815,623,645]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B4210B4DFCC133E0" box="[826,837,623,644]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetId="figure-355@2.[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Exeristes spp., female. 1 — E. roborator, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 3 — E. arundinis, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 4 — E. denticulator, holotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 5 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 6 — E. arundinis, fore tarsal claw (lateral view); 7 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, hind femur and tibia (lateral view); 8 — E. denticulator, holotype, hind tibia and tarsus (lateral view); 9 — E. denticulator, holotype, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view); 10 — E. roborator, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404124/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B4210B4DFCC133E0" box="[826,837,623,644]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor tip without a subapical tubercle (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B6220BAEFE0033C5" box="[313,388,652,674]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetId="figure-355@2.[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Exeristes spp., female. 1 — E. roborator, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 3 — E. arundinis, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 4 — E. denticulator, holotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 5 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 6 — E. arundinis, fore tarsal claw (lateral view); 7 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, hind femur and tibia (lateral view); 8 — E. denticulator, holotype, hind tibia and tarsus (lateral view); 9 — E. denticulator, holotype, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view); 10 — E. roborator, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404124/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
fig. 2, 
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B6620BAEFE0033C5" box="[377,388,652,673]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Female fore tarsal claws simple. Male scape, pedicel, fore and middle coxae, and all trochanters yellow; hind coxa black (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B54B0B8AFD0633DA" box="[592,642,680,702]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF2FF82B5900B8BFD1233DA" box="[651,662,681,702]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetId="figure-355@2.[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Exeristes spp., female. 1 — E. roborator, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 3 — E. arundinis, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 4 — E. denticulator, holotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 5 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 6 — E. arundinis, fore tarsal claw (lateral view); 7 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, hind femur and tibia (lateral view); 8 — E. denticulator, holotype, hind tibia and tarsus (lateral view); 9 — E. denticulator, holotype, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view); 10 — E. roborator, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404124/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF2FF82B5900B8BFD1233DA" box="[651,662,681,702]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). ............................................................................. 
